71.1	Rashomon_(film)	Rashomon (film)	Rashomon Rashōmon) is a 1950 Japanese crime drama film directed by Akira Kurosawa, working in close collaboration with cinematographer Kazuo Miyagawa. It stars Toshirō Mifune, Masayuki Mori, Machiko Kyō and Takashi Shimura. The film is based on two stories by Ryūnosuke Akutagawa — ("Rashomon" provides the setting, while "In a Grove" provides the characters and plot).	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a7/Rashomon_poster_2.jpg/220px-Rashomon_poster_2.jpg
